'''''Star Wars Journal: Hero for Hire''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] junior novel written by [[Donna Tauscher]]. It is part of the ''[[Star Wars Journal]]s'' series, and it was published by [[Scholastic]] in [[July]] [[1998]], in conjunction with ''[[Star Wars Journal: Captive to Evil]]'' and ''[[Star Wars Journal: The Fight for Justice]]''.

''Hero for Hire'' is presented as a group of [[in-universe]] [[Datapad/Legends|datapad]] entries recording a conversation between [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and the [[B'omarr Order/Legends|B'omarr monk]] [[Sai'da]], during the time Solo was captive in [[Jabba's Palace/Legends|Jabba's Palace]] in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]].

==Publisher's summary==
''In this book, Han Solo records his trials and adventures in Jabba the Hutt's dungeon.''

